{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to talk to you"},{"time":2000,"text":"about power in this 21st century."},{"time":4000,"text":"And basically, what I'd like to tell you"},{"time":7000,"text":"is that power is changing,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and there are two types of changes"},{"time":12000,"text":"I want to discuss."},{"time":14000,"text":"One is power transition,"},{"time":17000,"text":"which is change of power amongst states."},{"time":20000,"text":"And there the simple version of the message"},{"time":23000,"text":"is it's moving from West to East."},{"time":26000,"text":"The other is power diffusion,"},{"time":29000,"text":"the way power is moving"},{"time":31000,"text":"from all states West or East"},{"time":33000,"text":"to non-state actors."},{"time":36000,"text":"Those two things"},{"time":38000,"text":"are the huge shifts of power"},{"time":40000,"text":"in our century."},{"time":42000,"text":"And I want to tell you about them each separately"},{"time":45000,"text":"and then how they interact"},{"time":47000,"text":"and why, in the end, there may be some good news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"When we talk about power transition,"},{"time":54000,"text":"we often talk about the rise of Asia."},{"time":58000,"text":"It really should be called"},{"time":60000,"text":"the recovery or return of Asia."},{"time":62000,"text":"If we looked at the world"},{"time":64000,"text":"in 1800,"},{"time":66000,"text":"you'd find that more than half of the world's people"},{"time":69000,"text":"lived in Asia"},{"time":71000,"text":"and they made more than half the world's product."},{"time":74000,"text":"Now fast forward to 1900:"},{"time":77000,"text":"half the world's people -- more than half -- still live in Asia,"},{"time":80000,"text":"but they're now making"},{"time":82000,"text":"only a fifth of the world's product."},{"time":84000,"text":"What happened? The Industrial Revolution,"},{"time":87000,"text":"which meant that all of a sudden,"},{"time":89000,"text":"Europe and America"},{"time":91000,"text":"became the dominant center of the world."},{"time":94000,"text":"What we're going to see in the 21st century"},{"time":97000,"text":"is Asia gradually returning"},{"time":100000,"text":"to being more than half of the world's population"},{"time":103000,"text":"and more than half of the world's product."},{"time":107000,"text":"That's important and it's an important shift."},{"time":110000,"text":"But let me tell you a little bit about"},{"time":112000,"text":"the other shift that I'm talking about,"},{"time":114000,"text":"which is power diffusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"To understand power diffusion"},{"time":119000,"text":"put this in your mind:"},{"time":121000,"text":"computing and communications costs"},{"time":124000,"text":"have fallen a thousandfold"},{"time":127000,"text":"between 1970"},{"time":129000,"text":"and the beginning of this century."},{"time":131000,"text":"Now that's a big abstract number."},{"time":133000,"text":"But to make it more real,"},{"time":135000,"text":"if the price of an automobile"},{"time":137000,"text":"had fallen as rapidly"},{"time":139000,"text":"as the price of computing power,"},{"time":141000,"text":"you could buy a car today"},{"time":143000,"text":"for five dollars."},{"time":145000,"text":"Now when the price of any technology"},{"time":147000,"text":"declines that dramatically,"},{"time":150000,"text":"the barriers to entry go down."},{"time":153000,"text":"Anybody can play in the game."},{"time":155000,"text":"So in 1970,"},{"time":157000,"text":"if you wanted to communicate"},{"time":159000,"text":"from Oxford to Johannesburg"},{"time":161000,"text":"to New Delhi"},{"time":163000,"text":"to Brasilia"},{"time":165000,"text":"and anywhere simultaneously,"},{"time":168000,"text":"you could do it."},{"time":170000,"text":"The technology was there."},{"time":172000,"text":"But to be able to do it,"},{"time":174000,"text":"you had to be very rich --"},{"time":176000,"text":"a government, a multinational corporation,"},{"time":179000,"text":"maybe the Catholic Church --"},{"time":182000,"text":"but you had to be pretty wealthy."},{"time":184000,"text":"Now, anybody has that capacity,"},{"time":187000,"text":"which previously was restricted by price"},{"time":190000,"text":"just to a few actors."},{"time":193000,"text":"If they have the price of entry into an Internet cafe --"},{"time":196000,"text":"the last time I looked, it was something like a pound an hour --"},{"time":199000,"text":"and if you have Skype, it's free."},{"time":202000,"text":"So capabilities"},{"time":204000,"text":"that were once restricted"},{"time":206000,"text":"are now available to everyone."},{"time":208000,"text":"And what that means"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"is not that the age of the State is over."},{"time":214000,"text":"The State still matters."},{"time":216000,"text":"But the stage is crowded."},{"time":218000,"text":"The State's not alone. There are many, many actors."},{"time":221000,"text":"Some of that's good:"},{"time":223000,"text":"Oxfam,"},{"time":225000,"text":"a great non-governmental actor."},{"time":227000,"text":"Some of it's bad:"},{"time":229000,"text":"Al Qaeda, another non-governmental actor."},{"time":232000,"text":"But think of what it does"},{"time":234000,"text":"to how we think in traditional terms and concepts."},{"time":237000,"text":"We think in terms of war"},{"time":239000,"text":"and interstate war."},{"time":241000,"text":"And you can think back to 1941"},{"time":244000,"text":"when the government of Japan"},{"time":246000,"text":"attacked the United States at Pearl Harbor."},{"time":249000,"text":"It's worth noticing"},{"time":251000,"text":"that a non-state actor"},{"time":253000,"text":"attacking the United States in 2001"},{"time":256000,"text":"killed more Americans"},{"time":258000,"text":"than the government of Japan did in 1941."},{"time":261000,"text":"You might think of that"},{"time":263000,"text":"as the privatization of war."},{"time":265000,"text":"So we're seeing a great change"},{"time":268000,"text":"in terms of diffusion of power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271000,"text":"Now the problem is"},{"time":274000,"text":"that we're not thinking about it in very innovative ways."},{"time":277000,"text":"So let me step back"},{"time":279000,"text":"and ask: what's power?"},{"time":281000,"text":"Power is simple the ability"},{"time":283000,"text":"to affect others"},{"time":285000,"text":"to get the outcomes you want,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and you can do it in three ways."},{"time":289000,"text":"You can do it with threats"},{"time":291000,"text":"of coercion, \"sticks,\""},{"time":293000,"text":"you can do it with payments,"},{"time":295000,"text":"\"carrots,\""},{"time":297000,"text":"or you can do it by getting others"},{"time":299000,"text":"to want what you want."},{"time":301000,"text":"And that ability to get others to want what you want,"},{"time":304000,"text":"to get the outcomes you want"},{"time":306000,"text":"without coercion or payment,"},{"time":308000,"text":"is what I call soft power."},{"time":311000,"text":"And that soft power has been much neglected"},{"time":314000,"text":"and much misunderstood,"},{"time":316000,"text":"and yet it's tremendously important."},{"time":319000,"text":"Indeed, if you can learn"},{"time":322000,"text":"to use more soft power,"},{"time":324000,"text":"you can save a lot"},{"time":326000,"text":"on carrots and sticks."},{"time":328000,"text":"Traditionally, the way people thought about power"},{"time":331000,"text":"was primarily in terms of military power."},{"time":335000,"text":"For example, the great Oxford historian"},{"time":337000,"text":"who taught here at this university, A.J.P. Taylor,"},{"time":340000,"text":"defined a great power"},{"time":343000,"text":"as a country able to prevail in war."},{"time":347000,"text":"But we need a new narrative"},{"time":349000,"text":"if we're to understand power in the 21st century."},{"time":351000,"text":"It's not just prevailing at war,"},{"time":353000,"text":"though war still persists."},{"time":356000,"text":"It's not whose army wins;"},{"time":358000,"text":"it's also whose story wins."},{"time":361000,"text":"And we have to think much more in terms of narratives"},{"time":364000,"text":"and whose narrative is going to be effective."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"Now let me go back"},{"time":370000,"text":"to the question"},{"time":372000,"text":"of power transition"},{"time":374000,"text":"between states"},{"time":376000,"text":"and what's happening there."},{"time":378000,"text":"the narratives that we use now"},{"time":380000,"text":"tend to be the rise and fall"},{"time":382000,"text":"of the great powers."},{"time":384000,"text":"And the current narrative is all about"},{"time":386000,"text":"the rise of China"},{"time":388000,"text":"and the decline of the United States."},{"time":391000,"text":"Indeed, with the 2008 financial crisis,"},{"time":393000,"text":"many people said this was"},{"time":395000,"text":"the beginning of the end of American power."},{"time":397000,"text":"The tectonic plates"},{"time":399000,"text":"of world politics were shifting."},{"time":402000,"text":"And president Medvedev of Russia, for example,"},{"time":404000,"text":"pronounced in 2008"},{"time":406000,"text":"this was the beginning of the end"},{"time":408000,"text":"of United States power."},{"time":410000,"text":"But in fact,"},{"time":412000,"text":"this metaphor of decline"},{"time":414000,"text":"is often very misleading."},{"time":416000,"text":"If you look at history, in recent history,"},{"time":419000,"text":"you'll see the cycles of belief"},{"time":421000,"text":"in American decline"},{"time":423000,"text":"come and go every 10 or 15 years or so."},{"time":427000,"text":"In 1958,"},{"time":429000,"text":"after the Soviets put up Sputnik,"},{"time":431000,"text":"it was \"That's the end of America.\""},{"time":433000,"text":"In 1973, with the oil embargo"},{"time":435000,"text":"and the closing of the gold window,"},{"time":438000,"text":"that was the end of America."},{"time":440000,"text":"In the 1980s,"},{"time":442000,"text":"as America went through a transition in the Reagan period,"},{"time":444000,"text":"between the rust belt economy of the midwest"},{"time":447000,"text":"to the Silicon Valley economy of California,"},{"time":450000,"text":"that was the end of America."},{"time":453000,"text":"But in fact, what we've seen"},{"time":455000,"text":"is none of those were true."},{"time":458000,"text":"Indeed, people were over-enthusiastic"},{"time":461000,"text":"in the early 2000s,"},{"time":463000,"text":"thinking America could do anything,"},{"time":465000,"text":"which led us into some disastrous"},{"time":467000,"text":"foreign policy adventures,"},{"time":469000,"text":"and now we're back to decline again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":471000,"text":"The moral of this story"},{"time":473000,"text":"is all these narratives about rise and fall and decline"},{"time":476000,"text":"tell us a lot more about psychology"},{"time":479000,"text":"than they do about reality."},{"time":481000,"text":"If we try to focus on the reality,"},{"time":484000,"text":"then what we need to focus on"},{"time":486000,"text":"is what's really happening"},{"time":488000,"text":"in terms of China and the United States."},{"time":492000,"text":"Goldman Sachs has projected"},{"time":494000,"text":"that China, the Chinese economy,"},{"time":497000,"text":"will surpass that of the U.S."},{"time":500000,"text":"by 2027."},{"time":502000,"text":"So we've got, what,"},{"time":504000,"text":"17 more years to go or so"},{"time":506000,"text":"before China's bigger."},{"time":508000,"text":"Now someday,"},{"time":510000,"text":"with a billion point three people getting richer,"},{"time":512000,"text":"they are going to be bigger than the United States."},{"time":515000,"text":"But be very careful about these projections"},{"time":517000,"text":"such as the Goldman Sachs projection"},{"time":519000,"text":"as though that gives you an accurate picture"},{"time":522000,"text":"of power transition in this century."},{"time":525000,"text":"Let me mention three reasons why it's too simple."},{"time":528000,"text":"First of all, it's a linear projection."},{"time":531000,"text":"You know, everything says,"},{"time":533000,"text":"here's the growth rate of China, here's the growth rate of the U.S.,"},{"time":535000,"text":"here it goes -- straight line."},{"time":537000,"text":"History is not linear."},{"time":539000,"text":"There are often bumps along the road, accidents along the way."},{"time":542000,"text":"The second thing is"},{"time":544000,"text":"that the Chinese economy"},{"time":546000,"text":"passes the U.S. economy in, let's say, 2030,"},{"time":549000,"text":"which it may it,"},{"time":551000,"text":"that will be a measure of total economic size,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but not of per capita income --"},{"time":556000,"text":"won't tell you about the composition of the economy."},{"time":559000,"text":"China still has large areas"},{"time":561000,"text":"of underdevelopment"},{"time":563000,"text":"and per capita income is a better measure"},{"time":565000,"text":"of the sophistication of the economy."},{"time":567000,"text":"And that the Chinese won't catch up or pass the Americans"},{"time":570000,"text":"until somewhere in the latter part,"},{"time":572000,"text":"after 2050, of this century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"The other point that's worth noticing"},{"time":578000,"text":"is how one-dimensional"},{"time":580000,"text":"this projection is."},{"time":582000,"text":"You know, it looks at economic power"},{"time":584000,"text":"measured by GDP."},{"time":586000,"text":"Doesn't tell you much about military power,"},{"time":589000,"text":"doesn't tell you very much about soft power."},{"time":591000,"text":"It's all very one-dimensional."},{"time":593000,"text":"And also, when we think about the rise of Asia,"},{"time":596000,"text":"or return of Asia"},{"time":598000,"text":"as I called it a little bit earlier,"},{"time":600000,"text":"it's worth remembering Asia's not one thing."},{"time":603000,"text":"If you're sitting in Japan,"},{"time":606000,"text":"or in New Delhi,"},{"time":608000,"text":"or in Hanoi,"},{"time":610000,"text":"your view of the rise of China"},{"time":613000,"text":"is a little different than if you're sitting in Beijing."},{"time":616000,"text":"Indeed, one of the advantages"},{"time":618000,"text":"that the Americans will have"},{"time":620000,"text":"in terms of power in Asia"},{"time":622000,"text":"is all those countries"},{"time":624000,"text":"want an American insurance policy"},{"time":626000,"text":"against the rise of China."},{"time":628000,"text":"It's as though Mexico and Canada"},{"time":631000,"text":"were hostile neighbors to the United States,"},{"time":633000,"text":"which they're not."},{"time":635000,"text":"So these simple projections"},{"time":637000,"text":"of the Goldman Sachs type"},{"time":639000,"text":"are not telling us what we need to know"},{"time":641000,"text":"about power transition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"But you might ask, well so what in any case?"},{"time":645000,"text":"Why does it matter? Who cares?"},{"time":647000,"text":"Is this just a game"},{"time":649000,"text":"that diplomats and academics play?"},{"time":651000,"text":"The answer is it matters quite a lot."},{"time":654000,"text":"Because, if you believe in decline"},{"time":656000,"text":"and you get the answers wrong on this,"},{"time":659000,"text":"the facts, not the myths,"},{"time":661000,"text":"you may have policies which are very dangerous."},{"time":664000,"text":"Let me give you an example from history."},{"time":667000,"text":"The Peloponnesian War"},{"time":669000,"text":"was the great conflict"},{"time":671000,"text":"in which the Greek city state system"},{"time":673000,"text":"tore itself apart"},{"time":676000,"text":"two and a half millennia ago."},{"time":679000,"text":"What caused it?"},{"time":681000,"text":"Thucydides, the great historian of the the Peloponnesian War,"},{"time":684000,"text":"said it was the rise in the power of Athens"},{"time":687000,"text":"and the fear it created in Sparta."},{"time":690000,"text":"Notice both halves of that explanation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"Many people argue"},{"time":695000,"text":"that the 21st century"},{"time":697000,"text":"is going to repeat the 20th century,"},{"time":699000,"text":"in which World War One,"},{"time":702000,"text":"the great conflagration"},{"time":704000,"text":"in which the European state system"},{"time":706000,"text":"tore itself apart"},{"time":708000,"text":"and destroyed its centrality in the world,"},{"time":710000,"text":"that that was caused by"},{"time":712000,"text":"the rise in the power of Germany"},{"time":714000,"text":"and the fear it created in Britain."},{"time":717000,"text":"So there are people who are telling us"},{"time":719000,"text":"this is going to be reproduced today,"},{"time":721000,"text":"that what we're going to see"},{"time":723000,"text":"is the same thing now in this century."},{"time":726000,"text":"No, I think that's wrong."},{"time":728000,"text":"It's bad history."},{"time":730000,"text":"For one thing, Germany had surpassed Britain"},{"time":732000,"text":"in industrial strength by 1900."},{"time":734000,"text":"And as I said earlier,"},{"time":736000,"text":"China has not passed the United States."},{"time":739000,"text":"But also, if you have this belief"},{"time":741000,"text":"and it creates a sense of fear,"},{"time":744000,"text":"it leads to overreaction."},{"time":746000,"text":"And the greatest danger we have"},{"time":748000,"text":"of managing this power transition"},{"time":751000,"text":"of the shift toward the East is fear."},{"time":754000,"text":"To paraphrase Franklin Roosevelt"},{"time":756000,"text":"from a different context,"},{"time":758000,"text":"the greatest thing we have to fear is fear itself."},{"time":761000,"text":"We don't have to fear the rise of China"},{"time":764000,"text":"or the return of Asia."},{"time":766000,"text":"And if we have policies"},{"time":768000,"text":"in which we take it"},{"time":770000,"text":"in that larger historical perspective,"},{"time":772000,"text":"we're going to be able"},{"time":774000,"text":"to manage this process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"Let me say a word now"},{"time":778000,"text":"about the distribution of power"},{"time":780000,"text":"and how it relates to power diffusion"},{"time":783000,"text":"and then pull these two types together."},{"time":785000,"text":"If you ask how is power distributed in the world today,"},{"time":788000,"text":"it's distributed much like"},{"time":791000,"text":"a three-dimensional chess game."},{"time":794000,"text":"Top board:"},{"time":796000,"text":"military power among states."},{"time":798000,"text":"The United States is the only superpower,"},{"time":801000,"text":"and it's likely to remain that way"},{"time":803000,"text":"for two or three decades."},{"time":805000,"text":"China's not going to replace the U.S. on this military board."},{"time":808000,"text":"Middle board of this three-dimensional chess game:"},{"time":811000,"text":"economic power among states."},{"time":813000,"text":"Power is multi-polar."},{"time":816000,"text":"There are balancers --"},{"time":818000,"text":"the U.S., Europe,"},{"time":820000,"text":"China, Japan"},{"time":822000,"text":"can balance each other."},{"time":824000,"text":"The bottom board of this three-dimensional,"},{"time":827000,"text":"the board of transnational relations,"},{"time":829000,"text":"things that cross borders outside the control of governments,"},{"time":833000,"text":"things like climate change, drug trade,"},{"time":836000,"text":"financial flows,"},{"time":838000,"text":"pandemics,"},{"time":840000,"text":"all these things that cross borders"},{"time":842000,"text":"outside the control of governments,"},{"time":844000,"text":"there nobody's in charge."},{"time":846000,"text":"It makes no sense to call this unipolar"},{"time":848000,"text":"or multi-polar."},{"time":850000,"text":"Power is chaotically distributed."},{"time":852000,"text":"And the only way you can solve these problems --"},{"time":854000,"text":"and this is where many greatest challenges"},{"time":856000,"text":"are coming in this century --"},{"time":858000,"text":"is through cooperation,"},{"time":860000,"text":"through working together,"},{"time":862000,"text":"which means that soft power becomes more important,"},{"time":865000,"text":"that ability to organize networks"},{"time":867000,"text":"to deal with these kinds of problems"},{"time":869000,"text":"and to be able to get cooperation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":872000,"text":"Another way of putting it"},{"time":874000,"text":"is that as we think of power in the 21st century,"},{"time":877000,"text":"we want to get away from the idea"},{"time":879000,"text":"that power's always zero sum --"},{"time":881000,"text":"my gain is your loss and vice versa."},{"time":884000,"text":"Power can also be positive sum,"},{"time":887000,"text":"where your gain can be my gain."},{"time":890000,"text":"If China develops greater energy security"},{"time":893000,"text":"and greater capacity"},{"time":895000,"text":"to deal with its problems of carbon emissions,"},{"time":897000,"text":"that's good for us"},{"time":899000,"text":"as well as good for China"},{"time":901000,"text":"as well as good for everybody else."},{"time":903000,"text":"So empowering China"},{"time":905000,"text":"to deal with its own problems of carbon"},{"time":908000,"text":"is good for everybody,"},{"time":911000,"text":"and it's not a zero sum, I win, you lose."},{"time":914000,"text":"It's one in which we can all gain."},{"time":916000,"text":"So as we think about power"},{"time":918000,"text":"in this century,"},{"time":920000,"text":"we want to get away from this view"},{"time":922000,"text":"that it's all I win, you lose."},{"time":925000,"text":"Now I don't mean to be Pollyannaish about this."},{"time":928000,"text":"Wars persist. Power persists."},{"time":930000,"text":"Military power is important."},{"time":932000,"text":"Keeping balances is important."},{"time":934000,"text":"All this still persists."},{"time":936000,"text":"Hard power is there,"},{"time":938000,"text":"and it will remain."},{"time":940000,"text":"But unless you learn how to mix"},{"time":942000,"text":"hard power with soft power"},{"time":944000,"text":"into strategies that I call smart power,"},{"time":947000,"text":"you're not going to deal with the new kinds of problems"},{"time":949000,"text":"that we're facing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"So the key question that we need to think about as we look at this"},{"time":955000,"text":"is how do we work together"},{"time":957000,"text":"to produce global public goods,"},{"time":960000,"text":"things from which all of us can benefit?"},{"time":963000,"text":"How do we define our national interests"},{"time":965000,"text":"so that it's not just zero sum,"},{"time":967000,"text":"but positive sum."},{"time":969000,"text":"In that sense, if we define our interests,"},{"time":971000,"text":"for example, for the United States"},{"time":973000,"text":"the way Britain defined its interests in the 19th century,"},{"time":976000,"text":"keeping an open trading system,"},{"time":979000,"text":"keeping a monetary stability, keeping freedom of the seas --"},{"time":982000,"text":"those were good for Britain,"},{"time":984000,"text":"they were good for others as well."},{"time":986000,"text":"And in the 21st century, you have to do an analog to that."},{"time":989000,"text":"How do we produce global public goods,"},{"time":992000,"text":"which are good for us,"},{"time":994000,"text":"but good for everyone at the same time?"},{"time":996000,"text":"And that's going to be the good news dimension"},{"time":998000,"text":"of what we need to think about"},{"time":1000000,"text":"as we think of power in the 21st century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003000,"text":"There are ways to define our interests"},{"time":1006000,"text":"in which, while protecting ourselves with hard power,"},{"time":1009000,"text":"we can organize with others in networks"},{"time":1012000,"text":"to produce, not only public goods,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"but ways that will enhance our soft power."},{"time":1018000,"text":"So if one looks at the statements"},{"time":1021000,"text":"that have been made about this,"},{"time":1023000,"text":"I am impressed that when Hillary Clinton"},{"time":1025000,"text":"described the foreign policy"},{"time":1027000,"text":"of the Obama administration,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"she said that the foreign policy of the Obama administration"},{"time":1032000,"text":"was going to be smart power,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"as she put it, \"using all the tools"},{"time":1037000,"text":"in our foreign policy tool box.\""},{"time":1041000,"text":"And if we're going to deal"},{"time":1043000,"text":"with these two great power shifts that I've described,"},{"time":1046000,"text":"the power shift represented by transition among states,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"the power shift represented"},{"time":1051000,"text":"by diffusion of power away from all states,"},{"time":1054000,"text":"we're going to have to develop a new narrative of power"},{"time":1057000,"text":"in which we combine hard and soft power"},{"time":1060000,"text":"into strategies of smart power."},{"time":1063000,"text":"And that's the good news I have. We can do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1068000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}